         <abstract>
            <p>In the last decade academicians have developed an approach to analyzing a lessee's alternatives. It deals only with the form of fixed obligation to be assumed in association with the acquisition. This article presents and reconciles methods applying this approach and synthesizes earlier methods in a way that permits real differences distinguishing them to be reflected in the discount rates applied to lease obligations, uncertain operating flows, and tax shelters.</p>
         </abstract>
